Protagenic Therapeutics, Inc.

                    Protagenic Therapeutics, Inc. is a biotechnology company, which discovers and develops novel, naturally occurring human brain hormones for the treatment of anxiety and depression based mood disorders. It offers PT00114 and PT00121 peptide-based formulations. The company was founded by David A. Lovejoy and Hartounian Haro on February 3, 1994 and is headquartered in New York, NY.                  




