 Iroquois Financial Partners

“Iroquois Financial Partners (IFP) is a private investment firm specializing in lower middle market lending. IFP currently has $35 million of capital under management and is headquartered in Nashville, TN.”
Target Opportunity
We strive to fill a void created in today’s regulatory environment by providing debt financing to profitable, asset light lower middle market clients seeking between $1mm and $5mm in capital.
Creative Solutions
The IFP team understands the complexity of combining various types of financing alternatives. Our goal is to assist clients in creating the appropriate solution for both their short term needs and long term success. Our financing process is designed to create a partnership that enables management to concentrate on day-to-day operations.
Investment Criteria

Investment Size: $1 mm- $5mm
Investment Type: First Lien, Second lien, unitranche, and mezzanine term loans
Term: 12-60 months
Return Composition: Cash interest, accrued interest and warrants
Geographic Focus: USA
Use of Proceeds: Acquisition and growth financing, leverage buyouts, refinancings
Amortization: Excess cash flow sweeps, contractual and at maturity
Borrower Profile: Minimum LTM EBITDA of $500,000
Industry Focus: We are industry agnostic with a focus on strong growth potential, quality management and profitability

Value Proposition
Iroquois seeks to partner with proven management teams and financial sponsors to structure value-added financing solutions.
The investment team at Iroquois has expertise across many industries and transaction types.
Clients can trust that the team at Iroquois will:

Respond to every request and inquiry in a timely and professional manner
Commit to building value-enhancing relationships
Creatively solve complex financing needs through sensibly structured solutions
Maintain a streamlined execution process
Increase its capital commitment as client requirements expand with success

 


